# Learning more

## Online textbooks

Huge amount of resources at <https://psyteachr.github.io>.

- Data wrangling, visualization, and reports: [Applied Data Skills](https://psyteachr.github.io/ads-v2) microcredential course by Emily Nordmann & Lisa DeBruine
- [Level 1 ("Data Skills")](https://psyteachr.github.io/data-skills/) and [Level 2 ("Analysis")](https://psyteachr.github.io/analysis/) undergrad courses by Heather Woods, Emily Nordmann, Phil McAleer, Helena Paterson, Carolina Kuepper-Tetzel
- [Statistical modelling (Level 3) course](https://psyteachr.github.io/stat-models/) by Dale Barr

## Papers

- Nordmann, McAleer, Toivo, Paterson, DeBruine (2022). [Data Visualization using R for researchers who do not use R](https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.1177/25152459221074654).

- McAleer, et al. (submitted). [Embedding data skills in research methods education: Preparing students for reproducible research](https://psyarxiv.com/hq68s).
